            ; he lives at Nottingham, but he has a house in the parish <placeName id="t18330905-156-crimeloc878">of St. Michael, Wood-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18330905-156-crimeloc878" type="placeName" value="of St. Michael, Wood-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18330905-156-crimeloc878" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18330905-156-off877 t18330905-156-crimeloc878"></join> - I sleep there as servant to my father - on the 5th of August, about a quarter before twelve o'clock at night, I found the prisoner concealed inside a large hamper in the cellar; he was a total stranger to me, he must have got in before the doors closed at eight o'clock, as no part of the house was broken; or have let himself in with this skeleton key, which was found in the cellar, near where he was - I usually go into the cellar every night to see that all is right, and that night when I went down, the prisoner spoke before I saw him, and said, "I will surrender"; I then saw him, and had him taken.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18330905-156-person1540">
